-- Canada Confirms 11th E. Coli Case Linked to Meat From XL Foods
-- B y   L y d i a   M u l v a n y
-- 2012-10-08T20:46:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-08/canada-confirms-11th-e-coli-case-linked-to-meat-from-xl-foods.html
Canadian authorities confirmed an
11th case of E. coli lined to meat from XL Foods, a beef
processor in Alberta.  The latest case, in British Columbia, was confirmed today
by Gregory Taylor, deputy chief public officer of the Public
Health Agency of Canada, in a conference call with reporters.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lydia Mulvany in  New York  at 
 lmulvany1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
